">  </span><span class=\"n\">move_mul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">√</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mul_self_sqrt</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I tried to prove the goal,but lead to sub_goals:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">case</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e_x</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">e_a</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">e_a</span>\n<span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n<span class=\"n\">case</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e_x</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">hx</span>\n<span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n<span class=\"n\">case</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e_x</span>\n<span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n<span class=\"n\">case</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e_x</span>\n<span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In my opinion,they are obvious in math,because there are <code>Real.sqrt y</code>,<code>Real.sqrt x</code>and<code>Real.sqrt (x * y)</code>in the initial equation.But in lean,that doesn't seem to be the case</p>",
